<item>
            <title>[POOL-285] GenericKeyedObjectPool.returnObject() checks for idle object too late</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/POOL-285</link>
                <project id="12310488" key="POOL">Commons Pool</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;GenericKeyedObjectPool.returnObject() checks if the object was already returned to the pool after it has performed validation (if reqd) and after the object has been passivated.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This seems wrong - surely if the object has already been returned to the pool it should not be validated or passivated again?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
